<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Apple Pudding</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Kosher</cat>
        <cat>Desserts</cat>
        <cat>Fruits</cat></categories>
      <yield>12</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>5</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Med. size cooking apples</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Eggs, separated</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>White raisins</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Juice of 1/2 lemon</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Sugar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Matzo meal</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Peel, core and grate apples.  Sprinkle with lemon juice. Beat yolks until
  light.  Gradually beat in sugar, continuing to beat until thick. Stir in
  lemon juice, apples, matzo meal and raisins. Beat egg whites in separate
  bowl until stiff but not dry.  Fold whites into batter and pour into 2 1/2
  qt. greased casserole. Bake at 350 F. for 40 min. Serve hot.
  
  From Gemini's MASSIVE MealMaster collection at www.synapse.com/~gemini
 
</step></directions></recipe></recipeml>
